    "body" : "<p>The following solution is for my case.</p>\n<pre><code>import java.util.List;\nimport java.util.ArrayList;\n\npublic class HelloWorld{\n\n     public static void main(String []args){\n        List&lt;int[]&gt; result = new ArrayList&lt;&gt;();\n        result.add(new int[]{0, 0});\n        result.add(new int[]{1, 1});\n        result.add(new int[]{2, 2});\n        \n        // Method Reference to a Constructor\n        int[][] temp = result.toArray(int[][]::new);\n        for(int[] value: temp) {\n            System.out.println(&quot;{&quot; + value[0] + &quot;, &quot; + value[1] + &quot;}&quot;);\n        }\n     }\n}\n</code></pre>\n<ul>\n<li>Method Reference: <a href=\"https://docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/java/javaOO/methodreferences.html\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">https://docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/java/javaOO/methodreferences.html</a></li>\n<li>Method Reference to a Constructor: <a href=\"https://www.baeldung.com/java-method-references#constructor\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">https://www.baeldung.com/java-method-references#constructor</a></li>\n</ul>\n"
  } ],
